<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-04-07T13:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-04-07T13:00:00-05:00" n="136" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d136">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 European War 1939/9714:
                                Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Steinhardt</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-04-07T21:00:00+03:00">April
                                        7, 1941—9 p.m.</date>
                                    <lb/> [Received April 7—6:40 p.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>704. It has been reported to the Embassy, based on first hand
                                information, that quiet recruiting is now progressing in Moscow and
                                that engineering students have also been mobilized quietly and
                                dispatched to the German frontier for the purpose of erecting
                                defense works there.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Steinhardt</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>